    "extras": [
      "Best weather is usually April–June and September–October; shoulder-season mornings are cool enough for long old-city walks.",
      "Carry cash in Uzbek som for monuments, shared taxis and bazaar meals; card acceptance is improving but still inconsistent outside Tashkent.",
      "Afrosiyob seats sell out quickly around Nowruz and autumn weekends, so book the Tashkent–Samarkand–Bukhara legs a few days ahead.",
      "Most hotels handle mandatory foreigner registration automatically; keep one printed booking or registration slip just in case.",
      "For Khiva and Nukus transfers, shared taxis usually leave only when full, so agree on the fare before loading bags.",
      "If you only have one week, drop Nukus and Fergana Valley and focus on Tashkent, Samarkand, Bukhara and Khiva."
    ],
